cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper focuses on the achievable rates and throughput analysis of wireless networks, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless networks and their performance analysis, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper considers the cognitive ability of individual transmitters to optimize their coding rates, which can be seen as a form of multiagent systems. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the performance of wireless networks based on location information, which can be seen as a form of social and information networks. 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper considers two decoding rules and compares their performance, which can be seen as a form of game theory.
